Phungwayo, 29, and his brother, Phelelani Aubrey Phungwayo, were at a party in Spruitview, Ekurhuleni, during the May Day weekend when they were involved in an altercation with another man. The man was allegedly assaulted and he was shot at. The bullet hit his ring finger. The two brothers were arrested on Monday, but police failed to find the firearm that was allegedly used in the incident. Yesterday, magistrate Van der Hoevel granted the brothers bail of R2Â 000 each. The matter was postponed to June 23 for further investigations. - ANA